                            Funding Opportunities

   CDC's Procurement and Grants Office (PGO) is responsible for: 1) the
   awarding and administration of CDCÂ’s grants and cooperative agreements
   and those of the Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry
   (ATSDR); 2) the acquisition of program related health studies,
   professional services and research and development; and 3) the
   procurement of services, equipment, commodities, construction, and
   architectural and engineering services for CDC Programs.
